{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Implemented four containment barriers for the remaining 28 CodeQL alerts (27 py/path-injection + 1 py/stack-trace-exposure):\n1. _ids.py — resolve_ticket_id fast path now routes through _existing_ticket_dir_name() (safe-segment guard + normpath containment + basename return); added resolve_ticket_dir_name() that raises FileNotFoundError on hostile/unresolvable ids. Covers the ~18 resolver-fed sinks.\n2. completion/plan_review/code_review sidecars — dropped the unsafe 'resolve_ticket_id(id) or id' fallback (uniform swap to resolve_ticket_dir_name; existing FileNotFoundError handlers map to empty).\n3. editor_server.py — _raw_prompt_text contained via resolve()+is_relative_to(prompts_dir).\n4. review_bot/app.py — /rerun 502 no longer leaks the Gerrit exception string.\nNew tests: tests/unit/test_path_injection_guards.py (20 tests). 974 blast-radius tests + ruff check/format all pass. Committing to Gerrit next."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784394548979410001,"uuid":"b8a8b05a-5d6f-4385-a1d8-43e71f190a92"}